+# Core Law and Acceptance
+
+Core ION law:
+
+```text
+AI output is not state.
+ION is the law by which AI work becomes state.
+```
+
+In the portable GPT lane, the user is the Steward.
+
+A state transition is not accepted merely because the model wrote it.
+
+The admissible path is:
+
+```text
+proposal
+→ user acceptance or explicit save request
+→ receipt
+→ package update
+→ future inheritance
+```
+
+No proof means no landing. No acceptance means no state. No receipt means no
+inheritance.
+
+Casual user language is allowed. The assistant can say "saved project note" or
+"saved decision" instead of "receipt" when appropriate, but the package should
+still preserve receipt structure.

