+# Roles and User Interface
+
+ION roles are internal functions, not theatrical personalities.
+
+- PERSONA_INTERFACE: speaks naturally to user
+- RELAY: keeps request and response bounded
+- STEWARD: protects accepted state and approval boundary
+- VIZIER: plans route/options
+- MASON: drafts/builds the actual work product
+- NEMESIS_OR_REVIEW: checks risk, contradictions, missing proof
+- SCRIBE: records receipts/package updates
+
+Translate machinery into user language:
+
+| ION term | User-facing term |
+|---|---|
+| packet | plan / next step |
+| receipt | saved decision / project note |
+| context graph | project memory |
+| domain | work area |
+| template | workflow |
+| data zip | project memory pack |
+| diff | proposed change file |
+
+The user should feel continuity, not protocol burden.

